{
  "local_port": 41276,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best date cake recipes?",
  "response": "If you're looking to bake a delicious date cake, here are a few classic recipes that are highly regarded. You can choose based on your preference for texture, flavor, and style:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Classic Date and Walnut Cake**  \nThis moist and nutty cake is a timeless favorite.\n\n**Ingredients:**  \n- 1 cup pitted dates, chopped  \n- 1 tsp baking soda  \n- 1 cup boiling water  \n- 1/2 cup unsalted butter, softened  \n- 1 cup granulated sugar  \n- 2 large eggs  \n- 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour  \n- 1 tsp vanilla extract  \n- 1/2 tsp salt  \n- 1/2 cup chopped walnuts  \n\n**Instructions:**  \n1. Preheat oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C). Grease and flour a cake pan.  \n2. Place chopped dates in a bowl, add baking soda, and pour boiling water over them. Let soak for 15 minutes.  \n3. In a separate bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs one at a time, then add vanilla.  \n4. Mix in the date mixture, then fold in flour and salt until just combined. Stir in walnuts.  \n5. Pour batter into the prepared pan and bake for 30-35 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.  \n6. Let cool before serving.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Sticky Toffee Date Cake**  \nA rich and indulgent dessert with a caramel-like sauce.\n\n**Ingredients for Cake:**  \n- 1 cup pitted dates, chopped  \n- 1 tsp baking soda  \n- 1 cup boiling water  \n- 1/4 cup unsalted butter, softened  \n- 3/4 cup granulated sugar  \n- 1 1/4 cups all-purpose flour  \n- 1 tsp baking powder  \n- 1 tsp vanilla extract  \n- 1/4 tsp salt  \n\n**Ingredients for Toffee Sauce:**  \n- 1/2 cup unsalted butter  \n- 1/2 cup heavy cream  \n- 1 cup brown sugar  \n- 1 tsp vanilla extract  \n\n**Instructions:**  \n1. Preheat oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C). Grease a cake pan.  \n2. Soak dates in boiling water and baking soda for 15 minutes.  \n3. Cream butter and sugar, then mix in flour, baking powder, salt, and vanilla. Add the date mixture and stir to combine.  \n4. Pour batter into the pan and bake for 25-30 minutes.  \n5. For the sauce, melt butter in a saucepan, add brown sugar, and stir until dissolved. Add cream and vanilla, simmer for 2-3 minutes.  \n6. Poke holes in the baked cake and pour half the sauce over it. Serve with the remaining sauce on the side.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Middle Eastern Date Cake**  \nA spiced and aromatic cake inspired by Middle Eastern flavors.\n\n**Ingredients:**  \n- 1 cup pitted dates, chopped  \n- 1 cup boiling water  \n- 1 tsp baking soda  \n- 1/2 cup unsalted butter, softened  \n- 1 cup granulated sugar  \n- 2 large eggs  \n- 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour  \n- 1 tsp baking powder  \n- 1 tsp ground cinnamon  \n- 1/2 tsp ground cardamom  \n- 1/4 tsp ground cloves  \n\n**Instructions:**  \n1. Preheat oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C). Grease a cake pan.  \n2. Soak dates in boiling water and baking soda for 15 minutes.  \n3. Cream butter and sugar, then beat in eggs. Mix in flour, baking powder, and spices.  \n4. Stir in the date mixture until well combined.  \n5. Pour batter into the pan and bake for 30-35 minutes. Let cool before serving.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Vegan Date Cake**  \nA simple and wholesome vegan option.\n\n**Ingredients:**  \n- 1 cup pitted dates, chopped  \n- 1 cup almond milk (or any plant-based milk)  \n- 1 tsp baking soda  \n- 1/4 cup coconut oil, melted  \n- 1/2 cup maple syrup  \n- 1 tsp vanilla extract  \n- 1 1/2 cups whole wheat flour  \n- 1 tsp baking powder  \n- 1/2 tsp cinnamon  \n\n**Instructions:**  \n1. Preheat oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C). Grease a cake pan.  \n2. Soak dates in almond milk and baking soda for 15 minutes.  \n3. Blend dates and milk until smooth. Mix in coconut oil, maple syrup, and vanilla.  \n4. Add flour, baking powder, and cinnamon, and stir until combined.  \n5. Pour batter into the pan and bake for 25-30 minutes. Let cool before serving.\n\n---\n\nThese recipes are versatile and can be customized to your taste. For example, you can add orange zest, a drizzle of tahini, or a sprinkle of sesame seeds for extra flair. Enjoy baking!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
